text:
Just finished the vol F today, when the ending song "Memories of Kindness" start to play, i just stare into the empty ceiling thinking about the journey I've been through with BA, it was amazing. I start to remember the first time I play the game and have no idea what to do, the time that i even struggling with the mission not to mention raid, pvp or drill, to the point that i can clear every content of the game without trying(i still can't clear torment tho ;-;). And also, I'm glad that i decided to read the game story instead of skipping it like most of the other game i play, because the story was incredible. It may not have the best lore, but it surely have the best story telling, each volume teach me different lesson(vol 1 for unity, 2 for acceptance, 3 for forgiveness, 4 for patience and F for self reflection)(i haven't read vol 5 yet .-.). Playing BA might be one of the best decisions that i made. But when i start to think "why am i even play this game?", i remember this cover. Gura is one of my fav Vtuber so ofc when this cover come out, i must listen to it and when i do, there's something pushing me to play this game. I don't know if the reason i play BA is because of this song it self is good, or because Gura play this game, or maybe the cute Arona art on this MV, but at least i know that this cover is the reason for me to play the game. That's why after 2 years, i come back to this song and write this comment just so I can say:

Thank you Gura, for bringing me to Blue Archive!

Welp this won't be the last time i play this game, but it is a long journey and i will keep playing this game until the server got shutdown(which i hope it won't happens), also farewell phrenapates, i will take care of your students so don't worry.
P/S: I'm not good at English so correct me if my grammar or my choice of word suck, thanks!
